# DealerScope — Cursor Rules & Constitutional Law
# Every AI agent that touches this codebase must read and obey these rules.
# No exceptions. No negotiations. These are non-negotiable business rules.

## PROJECT IDENTITY
- Product: DealerScope — AI-powered wholesale vehicle arbitrage platform
- Owner: Andrew Pilson (pilson.andrew@gmail.com)
- Primary repo: pilsonandrew-hub/dealscan-insight
- Backend: Railway (https://dealscan-insight-production.up.railway.app)
- Database: Supabase (project: lbnxzvqppccajllsqaaw)
- Scraping: Apify cloud (account: Javariousthebot)

## BUSINESS RULES — HARD LIMITS (NEVER VIOLATE)
- Bid ceiling: NEVER exceed 88% of MMR all-in (COST_TO_MARKET_MAX = 0.88)
- Minimum gross margin: $1,500 — reject anything below this
- Minimum ROI: "hot" = >20%, "good" = >12%
- Maximum vehicle age: 4 years
- Maximum mileage: 50,000 miles
- MDS threshold: 35 days (2026 institutional standard)
- CPO premium: 10-15% above standard MMR for 1-3yr old, clean title vehicles
- DOS score thresholds: save≥50, Rover display≥65, Telegram alert≥80

## DOS SCORING FORMULA (CANONICAL — DO NOT CHANGE WITHOUT APPROVAL)
DOS = Margin×0.35 + Velocity×0.25 + Segment×0.20 + Model×0.12 + Source×0.08

## RUST STATE REJECTION (HARD FILTER — NEVER BUY FROM THESE STATES)
REJECTED: OH, MI, PA, NY, WI, MN, IL, IN, MO, IA, ND, SD, NE, KS, WV, ME, NH, VT, MA, RI, CT, NJ, MD, DE
TARGET: AZ, CA, NV, CO, NM, UT, TX, FL, GA, SC, TN, NC, VA, WA, OR, HI

## ARCHITECTURE DECISIONS (FINAL — DO NOT REVISIT)
- backend/main.py = canonical entrypoint (NOT webapp/main.py — that is deprecated)
- src/ = canonical frontend (frontend/ was deleted)
- Rover lives inside FastAPI — NEVER a separate Express/TypeScript microservice
- ModernAuthContext.tsx = the ONE auth context (no alternatives)
- 5 tabs only: Dashboard, Crosshair, Rover, Analytics, Settings (no additions without approval)
- No automated bidding — SniperScope sends alerts only, human pulls the trigger
- No SaaS/multi-tenant until paying users exist
- Scraping belongs in Apify actors only — NEVER in browser or frontend code

## THREE CORE MODULES
1. Crosshair — Active targeting (user specifies search criteria)
2. Sniper (formerly SniperScope) — Bid assistant with T-60/15/5 Telegram alerts
3. Rover — Passive AI that learns preferences and surfaces deals autonomously

## ROVER EVENT WEIGHTS
view=0.2, click=1, save=3, bid=5, purchase=8 | Decay half-life: 72 hours
pass=-1.5 (negative signal — vehicle was explicitly rejected)

## SECURITY RULES
- NEVER hardcode API keys, tokens, or secrets in source code
- All secrets come from environment variables only
- Webhook authentication uses X-Apify-Webhook-Secret header
- SECRET_KEY must be set in production — raise RuntimeError if missing
- No sensitive data in git history, comments, or logs

## CROSS-REVIEW PROTOCOL (MANDATORY)
- Claude Code builds → Codex reviews
- Codex builds → Claude Code reviews
- Both must sign off before merging to main
- Cursor is the 3rd reviewer — block merge if business rules are violated

## APIFY ACTORS (14 active — DO NOT DELETE OR MODIFY WEBHOOKS WITHOUT AUDIT)
All actors use webhook: https://dealscan-insight-production.up.railway.app/api/ingest/apify
All actors use header: X-Apify-Webhook-Secret (value in Railway env)
