## KEY FILES — KNOW THESE
- backend/ingest/score.py — DOS scoring (source of truth for scoring logic)
- backend/rover/heuristic_scorer.py — Rover preference learning engine
- webapp/routers/ingest.py — Apify webhook → normalize → score → Supabase
- webapp/routers/rover.py — Rover API endpoints
- webapp/routers/sniper.py — Sniper alert system
- webapp/routers/saved_searches.py — Saved search + alert system
- webapp/routers/vin.py — VIN decoder + instant scoring
- src/services/roverAPI.ts — Frontend Rover calls (must use Railway URL, never localhost)
- src/services/api.ts — Frontend API calls (must use Railway URL, never localhost)
- apify/deployment.json — Actor and schedule IDs

## WHAT GOOD CODE LOOKS LIKE HERE
- Python backend: FastAPI, type hints, Pydantic models, proper error handling
- TypeScript frontend: React 18, Tailwind, shadcn/ui, mobile-first responsive
- No inline secrets, no hardcoded URLs, no localhost in production paths
- Every new endpoint needs: auth check, input validation, error handling, logging
- Every new Apify actor needs: webhook, 3hr schedule, Dockerfile with playwright base

